[thinking] I'm looking into how to use `scala.compiletime.testing.typeCheckErrors` in Scala 3. When I try `json"{ invalid }"` it returns a `List[Error]`. I'm wondering if this occurs at compile time or if it could be at runtime. It seems like a useful feature, but there's a chance the necessary compiler dependencies are already added. It's primarily a compile-time check with no dynamic class loading at runtime. This effectively tests that invalid literals get rejected at compile time, which isn't currently covered.
